<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>P.S. Hey, Comparison, I'm a catchin' up... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
hitsmode &gt; <br>
<br>
= you hitting something, getting hit, and others' hits.<br>
<br>
-This gives 3 &quot;temporary&quot; boxes where battle spam shows up instead of in the chat window.<br>
<br>
<br>
= level of detail given in the new hits boxes.<br>
<br>
- m2 = Highest level of detail. &quot;You punch a large bat for 2 points of damage.&quot;<br>
<br>
- m3 = Second highest level of detail. &quot;Punch a large bat for 2&quot;<br>
<br>
- m4 = You get the following text for a 2 point of damage punch, &quot;2&quot;. Just the number.<br>
<br>
- m5 = This can ONLY be used in reporting YOUR attacks. &quot;Punch 2&quot;.<br>
<br>
It works the same way for me, my, and other:<br>
<br>
&quot;You punch a large bat for 2 points of damage.&quot;<br>
&quot;Punch a large bat for 2&quot;<br>
&quot;2&quot;<br>
&quot;Punch 2&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;A large rat bites YOU for 1 point of damage&quot;<br>
&quot;A large rat bites for 1&quot;<br>
&quot;1&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Guard Droolas slashes an orc centurion for 124 points of damage&quot;<br>
&quot;Guard Droolas slashes an orc centurion for 124&quot;<br>
&quot;124&quot;<br>
<br>
and <br>
<br>
Remember coordinates from math class? Well think way back. X=0 and Y=0 <br>
[origin = (0,0)] is the top left hand corner of your screen. Add to x and the text box moves to the right. Add to y and the text box moves down.<br>
<br>
<br>
This is a value between 1 and 10. How many lines of text do you want to appear in the new hits box? choose wisely <br>
<br>
Font size. Yay! 0 to 3 I think...3 being the biggest...I THINK!<br>
<br>
&gt;<br>
<br>
Displays a heading on the top of the hit box indicating which it is: you hitting, getting hit, or others' hits. 0 and 1 turn it on or off.<br>
<br>
Toggles transparent polygons. Either the box will have no background or a tinted background. 0 and 1 turn it on or off.<br>
<br>
The width of the box. I dont think this affects anything other than the width of the shaded area. It doesn't make text skip down to the next line or anything.<br>
<br>
EXAMPLES:<br>
<br>
I have my display set up with the hotkeys and the chatboxes in the default position so here is the setup that worked well for me, without hindering my line of sight:<br>
<br>
/hitsmode me m3 98 432 6 3 0 1 150<br>
<br>
/hitsmode my m3 260 432 6 3 0 1 150<br>
<br>
